# Copy to ".env" in the project root, then restart dev or run `npm run build && npx cap sync`.
#
# ── GitHub App (default: Marketplace + App Store friendly) ─────────────────
# Register at https://github.com/settings/apps → New GitHub App
#   • Enable "Device flow" (Required for this mobile/desktop client)
#   • Opt in to "User-to-server token expiration" in Optional features (recommended);
#     refresh works without a client_secret when tokens came from device flow.
#   • Repository permissions → Codespaces: Read and write (required to list/create
#     Codespaces via this app). Without it, GET /user/codespaces looks empty and
#     POST /user/codespaces returns "Resource not accessible by integration".
#   • Install the app under "Install App" for your user (and each org): choose "All
#     repositories" or explicitly add every repo you open in Mouse. User-to-server
#     tokens only reach repos the installation includes.
#   • Callback URL: e.g. http://localhost:5173/callback (required field; device flow still works)
# Marketplace: https://docs.github.com/en/apps/github-marketplace/overview/app-requirements-for-listing-in-github-marketplace
#
VITE_GITHUB_AUTH_KIND=github_app
# Optional: overrides the Client ID embedded in src/auth/GitHubAuth.ts
# VITE_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_app_client_id
#
# Public slug from github.com/apps/<slug> — required so sign-in can open the Install App flow.
# VITE_GITHUB_APP_SLUG=your_github_app_slug
#
# ── Legacy: classic OAuth App (not valid for GitHub Marketplace listing) ──
# VITE_GITHUB_AUTH_KIND=oauth_app
# VITE_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_oauth_app_client_id
# Optional override for device flow scopes (OAuth App only):
# VITE_GITHUB_DEVICE_SCOPES=codespace user:email
#
# ── Troubleshooting: missing Codespaces / "not accessible by integration" ─
# • GitHub App: bump Codespaces to Read and write, save, then re-authorize the
#   installation when GitHub prompts. Confirm the repo lives under an account/org
#   listed in that installation.
# • Or use oauth_app + codespace scope for a classic OAuth token that matches the web UI.
